claim: A photograph shows a 41-lb caught in New York City.
A photograph shows three buildings in New York decorated with window crosses for Easter in 1956.
A photograph shows two extremely muscular female bodybuilders.
A series of photographs show a UFO photographed over Memphis by several different people.
A photograph shows the phrase "Hail Satan" printed on the bottom of a cup from the In-N-Out Burger chain.
Two photographs of the earth taken by NASA in 1978 and 2012 document the dramatic effects of deforestation in North America.
An official movie poster shows Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson as the cartoon character Johnny Bravo.
A photograph documents Planned Parenthood founder Margaret Sanger speaking to women of the Ku Klux Klan (KKK).
Photographs show a cache of weapons uncovered by the Coast Guard in Greece, disguised as furniture and headed for European refugee camps.
A photograph shows President Obama posing next to a 69 or 420 mile marker.
A photograph shows Mr. Peebles, the "world's smallest cat."
A photograph shows a raccoon riding an alligator.
A 1955 photograph from Time magazine depicts what was considered that era's 'perfect body.'
A photograph shows giant humanoid skulls exposed by an earthquake or torrential rains.
Vintage color photograph from 1941 shows the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor.
Photograph shows a frozen Alaskan tree frog, a species that can survive for weeks with most of its body water frozen.
A man divorced his wife after he examined a photograph of her and spotted a man hiding under her bed.
A photograph shows a pregnant woman waiting to welcome home a military husband who couldn't have fathered the child she's carrying.
A “Welcome to Idaho” sign warns potential criminals about gun-owning citizens.
A photograph captures a cheerleader suffering an unfortunate bout of diarrhea in mid-air as her horrified teammates watch.
Photograph shows boxes of Tyson "[inverted] boneless pork rectums."
Image shows a fourth-grade science quiz about 'Dinosaurs: Genesis and the Gospel' from a South Carolina school.
A photograph shows an anti-rape device known as RapeX, a female condom with teeth lining the inside.
A photograph shows workmen who accidentally trapped their van within a barrier of bollards.
Photographs show an enormous bear killed by an Alaskan hunter.
A photograph shows an overhead view of shadows cast by camels in the desert.
